parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to fall into the door, making it difficult or impossible to operate, and potentially leading to safety and security issues, such as exposure to the elements, vandalism, or even accidents.
symptoms: The window falls into the door
the window will not come back up
the window comes off the track
the window makes a cracking noise
the window slams down into the door panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pan can cause the engine to lose oil, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the mass air flow sensor can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to stalling, decreased fuel economy, and decreased engine performance.
The failure of the window regulator can cause the window to become stuck, leading to inconvenience and potentially causing safety issues.
The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag light illuminating on the dashboard, indicating a potential safety risk, and in the event of an accident, the airbags may not deploy, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident
the driver's side airbag switch fails
